  "prompt": "How can I apply for my car to be on Overhaulin'?",
  "response": "To apply for your car to be featured on the show \"Overhaulin',\" you generally need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Official Website**: Go to the show's website to find any application forms or guidelines they might have provided.\n\n2. **Check Eligibility Requirements**: Ensure you meet any criteria they have for participants. This usually includes specifics about the condition and type of car they are looking to work on.\n\n3. **Prepare Your Application**: Typically, you will need to provide:\n   - Personal information\n   - Detailed information about your car including make, model, year, and its current condition\n   - The reason you want your car overhauled\n   - Photos of the car from various angles, both interior and exterior\n   - Any interesting or unique stories related to your car that might make your application stand out\n\n4. **Submit the Application**: Follow the instructions on the website for submission, which might be via an online form, email, or physical mail.\n\n5. **Wait for a Response**: After submission, the production team will review applications. If your car is selected, they will contact you with further steps.\n\nRemember that \"Overhaulin'\" typically chooses cars with a compelling story and significant sentimental value, so highlighting these aspects in your application can improve your chances. Additionally, it's useful to check social media channels and any community forums related to the show for updates or additional advice on applying.\n\nSince shows like \"Overhaulin'\" can have changes in their submission processes, it's important to refer to the most current information available on their official platforms.",
